Mental health map

top layer

df_cities = df %>%
  filter(geographic_level == "City",
         measure == "Mental health not good for >=14 days among adults aged >=18 Years",
         data_value_type == "Crude prevalence") %>%
  mutate(
    lat = str_extract(geo_location, "-?\\d+\\.?\\d*") %>% 
      as.numeric(),# %>% 
    #round(1),
    lon = str_extract(geo_location, "\\s-?\\d+\\.?\\d*") %>% 
      as.numeric() %>% #round(1) %>% 
      str_trim(c("both"))
  ) %>% 
  select(city_name, lat, lon, data_value) %>% 
  distinct()

p = df_cities %>%
  plot_mapbox(
    lat = ~lat,
    lon = ~lon,
    color = ~data_value,
    marker = list(),
    type = 'scattermapbox',
    hovertext = df_cities[,"city_name"]
  ) %>%
  layout(
    mapbox = list(
      style = 'dark',
      accesstoken = token,
      zoom = 2.5, # their's is 4, minZoom = 3, maxZoom = 12
      center = list(lon = -96.416, lat = 37.58))
  )

p
## No scattermapbox mode specifed:
##   Setting the mode to markers
##   Read more about this attribute -> https://plot.ly/r/reference/#scatter-mode

bottom layer scatter

df_tracts = df %>%
  filter(geographic_level == "Census Tract",
         measure == "Mental health not good for >=14 days among adults aged >=18 Years",
         data_value_type == "Crude prevalence") %>%
  mutate(
    lat = str_extract(geo_location, "-?\\d+\\.?\\d*") %>% 
      as.numeric(),# %>% 
    #round(1),
    lon = str_extract(geo_location, "\\s-?\\d+\\.?\\d*") %>% 
      as.numeric() %>% #round(1) %>% 
      str_trim(c("both"))
  ) %>% 
  select(city_name, lat, lon, data_value, city_fips, tract_fips) %>% 
  distinct()

p_base = df_tracts %>%
  plot_mapbox(
    lat = ~lat,
    lon = ~lon,
    color = ~data_value,
    marker = list(),
    type = 'scattermapbox',
    hovertext = df_cities[,"city_name"]
  ) %>%
  layout(
    mapbox = list(
      style = 'dark',
      accesstoken = token,
      zoom = 2.5, # their's is 4, 
      minZoom = 10, 
      maxZoom = 12.5,
      center = list(lon = -96.416, lat = 37.58))
  )

p_base
## No scattermapbox mode specifed:
##   Setting the mode to markers
##   Read more about this attribute -> https://plot.ly/r/reference/#scatter-mode

testing layers

p = df_cities %>%
  plot_mapbox(
    lat = ~lat,
    lon = ~lon,
    #color = "blue",
    marker = list(color = "blue", size = 10),
    type = 'scattermapbox',
    hovertext = df_cities[,"city_name"]
  ) %>%
  layout(
    mapbox = list(
      style = 'dark',
      accesstoken = token,
      zoom = 2.5, # their's is 4, minZoom = 3, maxZoom = 12
      center = list(lon = -96.416, lat = 37.58))
  )

p %>% 
  add_trace(
    data = df_tracts,
    lat = ~lat,
    lon = ~lon,
    #color = "red",
    marker = list(color = "red", size = 5),
    type = 'scattermapbox',
    hovertext = df_cities[,"city_name"]
  ) %>%
  layout(
    mapbox = list(
      style = 'dark',
      accesstoken = token,
      zoom = 2.5, # their's is 4, minZoom = 3, maxZoom = 12
      minZoom = 10, 
      maxZoom = 12,
      center = list(lon = -96.416, lat = 37.58))
  )

testing choropleth

ny = get_acs(geography = "tract", 
              variables = "B19013_001", 
              state = "NY", 
              county = "New York", 
              geometry = TRUE,
              key = "ae24453f5cbe5a92b368876f673eafffbec7b673")
## Getting data from the 2013-2017 5-year ACS
mapview(ny, zcol = "estimate", legend = TRUE)
mh_values = df_tracts %>% 
  select(tract_fips, data_value) %>% 
  drop_na()

ny_joined = left_join(ny, mh_values,
               by = c(GEOID = "tract_fips"))

mapview(ny_joined, zcol = "data_value", legend = TRUE)
